samples.sample:
Tom and Sue are friends. They like to play together. One day, they visit a new country with their moms. The country has many animals and trees.

"Look, Tom, a big lion!" Sue says. She points to a cage. The lion has yellow fur and sharp teeth.

"Wow, Sue, he is scary!" Tom says. He holds his mom's hand. He does not want to go near the cage.

But Sue is careless. She runs to the cage. She wants to touch the lion. She does not listen to her mom.

"Sue, stop! It is dangerous!" her mom shouts. She runs after Sue.

But it is too late. Sue puts her hand through the bars. The lion bites her hand. Sue screams. She is hurt.

Tom and his mom hear Sue scream. They run to help her. They see blood on her hand.

"Oh, Sue, you are silly!" Tom says. He is sad and angry. He does not want Sue to be hurt.

"I'm sorry, Tom. I'm sorry, mom. I was careless. I wanted to see the lion. I did not think he would bite me." Sue says. She cries. She is sorry and scared.

Her mom hugs her. She calls a doctor. The doctor comes and helps Sue. He puts a bandage on her hand. He says she will be okay.

Tom and his mom hug Sue too. They say they are glad she is okay. They say they still love her. But they also say she has to be careful. She has to listen to her mom. She has to respect the animals.

Sue nods. She says she learned her lesson. She says she will be careful. She says she loves Tom and her mom too.

They all smile. They decide to leave the lion alone. They go to see other animals. They have fun. They enjoy their visit to the new country.

Jill was a three year old girl. She lived with her grandma, who was elderly. One day, Jill wanted to play with her robot. But grandma was worried.

Jill asked "Why are you worried, Grandma?" 
Grandma replied, "I'm worried about you playing with the robot. It might be dangerous."

Jill understood why grandma was worried. She said, "It's ok, I'll be careful. I won't do anything unsafe. I promise!"

Grandma was still a bit worried, but she smiled and said, "Ok, you can play with the robot. Just make sure you're safe."

Jill thanked Grandma and went off to play with her robot. She enjoyed herself, but she made sure to stay safe!

Sam was skipping happily down the street. The sun shone brightly above, and a soft breeze blew across his face. 

As he skipped, he noticed a flame nearby. It was small and harmless, so he stopped to get a better look. He gazed in wonder at the bright bright flame, watching it flicker and dance. 

Sam wanted to get closer to the flame, but he was a little scared. He thought to himself, "Maybe I shouldn't get too close to the flame! It's so pretty, but it could hurt me."

But then, Sam stopped worrying and decided to skip around the flame, keeping a safe distance away. He skipped around it, making big circles and having lots of fun. Eventually, he skipped away and left the harmless flame behind. 

At the end of his journey, Sam was filled with happiness. He had seen the beautiful flame and skipped around it without getting hurt. It was a very special day!

Once upon a time, there was a chef named Anna who loved to work in her kitchen. Every day she would experiment with different ingredients and create delicious meals for the people in her city. 

One day she decided to try something new. She pulled out a menu, looked through it carefully and started to work. She thought of a delicious new dish that everyone would love. 

The next day she opened her restaurant and served her delicious new dish. Everyone was amazed at how delicious it tasted and they were so amazed that they lined up at her restaurant every day to eat it. 

The chef Anna was so happy - she had created something incredible that everyone loved. From then on, she worked carefully in the kitchen to make sure the people in her city could enjoy the same delicious meal day after day.

Lily and Ben are twins. They like to play in their room. They have many toys and books. But their favorite thing to play with is their mattress.

One day, they ask their mom if they can take the mattress off the bed and put it on the floor. Mom says yes, but they have to be careful and not make a mess. Lily and Ben are very happy. They drag the mattress to the middle of the room and jump on it.

"Look at me, I'm a frog!" Lily says, hopping up and down. "Ribbit, ribbit!"

"I'm a lion!" Ben says, roaring and crawling on the mattress. "Rawr, rawr!"

They pretend to be different animals and make funny noises. They laugh and giggle. They have so much fun.

Mom comes to check on them. She sees them playing on the mattress. She smiles and joins them.

"Can I be an animal too?" she asks.

"Sure, Mom!" Lily and Ben say. "What do you want to be?"

Mom thinks for a moment. Then she says, "I want to be a monkey!"

She makes funny faces and sounds. She tickles Lily and Ben. They squeal and hug her.

They all have a great time on the mattress. They are a happy family.

Once upon a time, there was a little car named Bobby. Bobby had four round tires. He liked to be organized and always had his tires in a neat line. Bobby loved to drive around and play with his friends.

One day, Bobby was driving very fast. He did not see a big rock on the road. "Oh no!" cried Bobby as he hit the rock. One of his tires suffered a big boo-boo. It hurt a lot. Bobby was sad because he could not play with his friends anymore.

Bobby's friends saw that he was sad. They wanted to help him. They found a new tire for Bobby. They worked together to put the new tire on Bobby. Now, Bobby was organized and happy again. Bobby thanked his friends and they all played together. And they all lived happily ever after.

Once upon a time, there was a mommy and a daddy, who both had a big red apron. They said it was time to bake a cake. Daddy said, "Let's put on our aprons before we start." 

The mommy and daddy put on their aprons to protect their clothes while they were baking. The mommy looked in the cupboard and had all the things she needed to make the cake, but the daddy was being selfish. He wanted to keep one of the ingredients.

The mommy said, "Don't be selfish, Daddy! We need to share all of the things to make the cake. We can save some of the pieces for later."

The daddy smiled and said, "You're right, Mommy. Let's do it together." He gave the last ingredient to the mommy and they both worked together to make the most delicious cake ever!

Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Anna. She was 3 years old and had a big yellow dress. Anna liked to wear the dress everywhere she went.

One day, Anna asked her mum, "Can I have some yummy tea?" Her mum said yes and made Anna a cup of tea. Anna sat at the table and drank her tea. She was enjoying it so much that she didn't want it to end.

Suddenly, Anna's mum said, "Anna, don't drink too much, it's too hot for you." But Anna just kept drinking.

Soon, her cup was empty and she felt unwell. She started to cough and felt needles in her tongue. Anna had burned her tongue with the hot tea.

Anna's mum helped her to dress and put a cold cloth on her tongue. Then Anna had to rest in her bed.

The end.
